detaileddescription.para: The operator that reads the splits received from the preceding {}. Contrary to the StreamingMonitorFunction} which has a parallelism of 1, this operator can have multiple parallelism. As soon as a split descriptor is received, it is put in a queue, and use {} read the actual data of the split. This architecture allows the separation of the reading thread from the one split processing the checkpoint barriers, thus removing any potential back-pressure.
